 &lt;a data-clipboard-text="https://tmcdigitech.github.io/dit11/appdev/basics/widgets/#the-check-box-kivy-widget" class="gdoc-page__anchor gdoc-page__anchor--right clip" aria-label="Anchor The Check Box Kivy Widget" href="#the-check-box-kivy-widget">
 &lt;svg class="icon gdoc_link">&lt;use xlink:href="#gdoc_link">&lt;/use>&lt;/svg>
 &lt;/a>
 &lt;/h2>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Let’s start with the check box Kivy widget. The check box is a two-state button that can be either checked or unchecked. Later we’ll see that it can be used as a radio button as well, if it’s in a group, but for now let’s just have a look at a single check box.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>